# Weather-Based Wardrobe Assistant (MVP Focus)

## Project Architecture
- Expo/React Native with TypeScript
- State Management: Context API (Redux only after MVP)
- Navigation: React Navigation
- API Integration: OpenWeatherMap
- Local Storage: AsyncStorage (Firebase after MVP)

## Development Workflow
- Follow specifications.md strictly for feature tracking
- Complete all MVP features before advancing to "Further features"
- Mark tasks as completed with [x] in specifications.md
- Add tests before marking features complete

## Git Workflow
- Main branch: stable releases only
- Develop branch: integration branch
- Feature branches: named feature/[feature-name]
- Test branches: named test/[feature-name]
- Commit message format: "[Feature/Fix/Refactor]: Brief description"

## MVP First Approach
- No implementation of "Further features" until ALL MVP items are complete
- Validate each MVP feature with manual testing before marking complete
- Document all completed features in README.md
